article.description: Harald Frey had 17 points to lead five Montana State players in double figures as the Bobcats topped Idaho 86-72 on Saturday. Keljin Blevins added 16 points for the Bobcats. Devin Kirby chipped in 14, Sam Neumann scored 13 and Tyler Hall had 13.
article.headline: Frey, Blevins lift Montana St. over Idaho 86-72
article.linkText: Frey, Blevins lift Montana St. over Idaho 86-72
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- Harald Frey had 17 points to lead five Montana State players in double figures as the Bobcats topped Idaho 86-72 on Saturday. Keljin Blevins added 16 points for the Bobcats. Devin Kirby chipped in 14, Sam Neumann scored 13 and Tyler Hall had 13. Cameron Tyson had 14 points for the Vandals (4-19, 1-11 Big Sky Conference), who have now lost nine straight games. Jared Rodriguez added 12 points and eight rebounds. Trevon Allen had 12 points. The Bobcats improve to 2-0 against the Vandals for the season. Montana State defeated Idaho 77-67 on Jan. 10. Montana State (11-12, 8-5) takes on Idaho State on the road on Thursday. Idaho plays Northern Colorado at home on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
